x
 3\sin x + 4\cos x = 5 
\tan (x/2) 
\begin{align} &3\sin x + 4\cos x = 5 \\ &\implies \dfrac 3 5\sin x + \dfrac 4 5 \cos x = 1 \\ &\implies \cos ( x - \arccos(\dfrac 4 5) ) = 1 \\ &\implies x = 2n\pi + \arccos(\dfrac 4 5) \\ &\implies x/2 = n\pi + 0.5\arctan(\dfrac 3 4)\\ &\implies \tan(x/2) = + \tan(0.5 \arctan(\dfrac 3 4)) = y \;\; \text{ (say)} \end{align}
 y = 3, -\dfrac 1 3 
 \dfrac{2y}{1-y^2} = \tan (\arctan(\dfrac 3 4 ) ) =  \dfrac 3 4 
\begin{align} &3\sin x + 4\cos x = 5 \\ &\implies \dfrac 3 5 \dfrac{ 2t } { 1 + t^2 } + \dfrac 4 5 \dfrac{ 1 - t^2 } { 1 + t^2 } = 1 \;\;\;\;(t = \tan (x/2))\\ &\implies (3t-1)^2 = 0 \implies t = \dfrac 1 3 \end{align}
 \dfrac{2y}{1-y^2} =  \dfrac 3 4 
 y = -3, \dfrac 1 3 
